Definition: a change in the electrical properties of the skin in response to stress or anxiety
Example: can be measured either by recording the electrical resistance of the skin or by recording weak currents generated by the body
Synonyms: GSR, psychogalvanic_response, electrodermal_response, electrical_skin_response, Fere_phenomenon, Tarchanoff_phenomenon, reaction, noun, artifact, lie_detector, p, a, change, in, the, electrical, properties, of, skin, response, to, stress, or, anxiety, can, be, measured, either, by, recording, resistance, weak, currents, generated, body
Category: noun.act
